      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAF ATTACK (2) raced wide and fought with the apprentice all the way last Saturday over 1800m at this track, eventually dropping right out. Form in two runs prior to that was good enough. Like the engagement of Maloney. First try at the mile-and-a-half - trust Ciaron Maher has him in the right race. LIBERTY PARK (4) stepped out beyond ten furlongs for the first time and scored an impressive win last time out at Doomben, coming from well back to score. Up sharply in grade but drops 4kgs and looks sure to appreciate the extra trip today. KUREDER (3) has not won for well over two years. Just behind the placegetters at his last three runs, all in the 2200-2400m range. Races best at this circuit, with two wins from two here at the trip. Can feature with Angela Jones to ride. MR O'REILLY (5) battled on well for a close third here last weekend and is likely to play a key role again on the limit weight. ALDEENAARY (6) is a risk at the trip but with just 49kgs is in the mix.",
